[SN]TITLE[SN]
Large mountain fire breaks out above Llangollen

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Firefighters are dealing with a large mountain fire in Denbighshire which broke out on Wednesday evening.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
About two hectares (five acres) of heather is alight along the Panorama Walk below the Eglwyseg escarpment, above Llangollen.
The area is a Site of Special Scientific interest.
The fire is ongoing, with firefighters from Llangollen, Wrexham, Buckley and Chirk using hosereel jets and beaters to try to control the blaze.
